<p>TV firmware updates including Cast shell, shall be supported using the r=
equired agent defined as Qterics (formerly <span class=3D"legacy-color-text=
-default">UpdateLogic Inc or ULI)</span>. &nbsp;Qterics is also the require=
d agent for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Provisioning.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"id-6.Updates-6.1SoftwareUpdatesforTVFirmware">6.1 &nbsp;Software =
Updates for TV Firmware</h2>
<p>SmartCast shall support 3 methods to updates TV firmware: Binary package=
 update, UTV update and Internet update.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"0b=
b3de39-e190-44cf-8ef6-31937dbcfc4c" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col style=3D"width: 760.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Software Update Methods</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>SOC binary package updates. After AC cycle with USB inserted, an update =
of the binary image proceeds. If compatible with SOC firmware and signature=
, this update is loaded by a low level loader. Even if everything from the =
kernel on up is broken, this firmware still loads. AC on version clears out=
 all firmware leaving TV in a low level. &nbsp;On update completion, OOBE i=
s presented. This is a&nbsp;more comprehensive update that will be limited =
to VIZIO, ODMs, SoC provider, certain partners and support.&nbsp;Not for cu=
stomers. &nbsp;USB package update is the only method to roll back firmware =
and is required to wipe certs and then TV must be re-registered.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Name <span data-colorid=3D"uehhnko91m">the file with format&nbsp;mgXXX-C=
ommandStickName.cmd.Name </span></p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Qterics UTV updates. The USB includes the standard Qterics packaged form=
at for the latest firmware update. The same as a firmware update delivered =
via OTA but loaded on USB. &nbsp;Firmware update only. &nbsp;The TV must be=
 powered on and functional, and the Qterics Agent (client) active for this =
firmware to load.</p>
<p>Obtain the UTV file by download using the =E2=80=9Ccloud=E2=80=9D icon o=
n 2020 NOC access page. &nbsp; Name the file with the&nbsp;format mg302-upd=
atename.utv with =E2=80=9Cupdatename=E2=80=9D the part you can change (e.g.=
 "mg302-1.1.6.1-5.utv"). NOTE:&nbsp;updatelogic.txt is no longer in use for=
 2020 and beyond.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Qterics Internet update. This is the Qterics Internet image. It contains=
 the same core firmware as the UTV.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"id-6.Updates-6.1.1SoftwareUpdateRequirements">6.1.1 Software Upda=
te Requirements</h3>
<p>SmartCast <span data-colorid=3D"bfefswu1ei">TV</span> shall support 3 me=
thods to updates TV firmware: Binary package update, UTV update and Interne=
t update.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"3e=
82a99b-03ea-4099-8d06-f5be61f83737" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Requirement</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>SmartCast TV shall support 3 methods to updates TV firmware:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Binary package update</p></li>
<li>
<p>UTV update</p></li>
<li>
<p>Internet update (OTA).</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>In any of the 3 methods, the appropriate security requirements shall be =
implemented to satisfy the security requirements for an unauthorized upgrad=
e or a bogus application.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The system shall support the ability to update the TV firmware through Q=
terics over IP.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All but the lowest level loader must be updateable, including the main S=
oC and programmable peripheral chips.&nbsp;This includes but is not limited=
 to:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Wi-Fi modules</p></li>
<li>
<p>Bluetooth modules</p></li>
<li>
<p>TCon/Gamma modules.</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>After&nbsp;factory reset or at initial OOBE, network connected, after <s=
pan data-colorid=3D"xiegjo5i0x">OTA</span> firmware update then&nbsp;SCPL D=
LM downloads assets and installs. SmartCast, binaries and TV is then comple=
tely up-to-date.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The TV&nbsp;shall contain multiple copies of the system software in orde=
r to recover a bad upgrade.&nbsp; Provisions must be made to account for an=
y power interruption or loss or network connectivity during upgrade in the =
field or at the factory.&nbsp;In the event of a corrupt or bad upgrade see =
RECOVERY section.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">7</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Platform shall implement and maintain ping pong partitions to store and =
execute previous firmware and current firmware that is being updated. In ca=
se of failure platform shall revert back to the previous firmware image to =
boot and retry. &nbsp;Also platform shall have a space for Golden build to =
revert to with minimum functions such as network and update when both ping/=
pong partitions fail. &nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">8</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The TV is powered on during an update. &nbsp;</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>After TV powered down the TV wakes up in the background (LED off) <span =
data-colorid=3D"q5ic54mkf3">about a minute after power off</span> to check =
for, and if found, download the update.</p></li>
<li>
<p>TV powered on during update, then TV cannot be powered down to allow&nbs=
p;firmware&nbsp;install of the update.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Check for updates, during&nbsp;firmware&nbsp;install, TV cannot be power=
ed down to allow completion of the update.</p></li>
</ol></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"id-6.Updates-6.1.1Internet(OTA)Updates">6.1.1 Internet (OTA) Upda=
tes</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d0=
36f59d-f6f6-43d0-9b9a-86a2f2a018e4" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh"></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Internet (OTA) Updates Requirements</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The Internet or over-the air (OTA) based update shall be implemented usi=
ng the framework provided by Qterics UpdateTV.&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>UpdateTV requires a socket interface for the command and control communi=
cation with their Network Operating Center (NOC).&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Three ways to receive the OTA update:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Check for update (update immediately, override all timers)</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>TV remains powered on but unavailable for viewing during the update proc=
ess. &nbsp;Powering down during update should be avoided: &nbsp;kills the u=
pdate.&nbsp;</p></li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p>Background Update:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>1 minute after TV powered off as per query pacing logic defined below. &=
nbsp;At launch checks daily at power down as per =E2=80=9CQuery Pacing Logi=
c=E2=80=9D below but as TV ages query increased to every 7 days. &nbsp;</p>=
</li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p>Background Update:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>If TV is not powered on then TV wakes up daily to check for update based=
 on query pacing logic as per =E2=80=9CQuery Pacing Logic=E2=80=9D below.</=
p></li>
</ol></li>
</ol></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Query Pacing Logic</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Gated by query pacing logic at power down, after 1 minute or if powered =
down, 1 day, the board powers on, then the SMARTCAST UpdateTV client sends =
an inquiry to the NOC periodically asking if any updates are available.</p>=
</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If an update is available</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>TV client downloads the update. &nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>TV installs the downloaded update.&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>TV reboots to complete the install.&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">7</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>TV powers down again.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">8</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>At the next power on, TV is running the new firmware and a notification =
of the update displays.&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">9</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>After the install is completed, wait 1 minute to check again for <span d=
ata-colorid=3D"jdzljz3gr2">DLM</span> binaries for the new install.</p></td=
>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">10</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If <span data-colorid=3D"lzcfk58gxv">DLM</span> binaries are available&n=
bsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Downloads the updated DLM binaries. &nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>TV installs the downloaded DLM binaries.&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">11</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>TV communicates&nbsp;to Qterics NOC via HTTPS but the UpdateTV client sh=
all download the encrypted image via HTTP from VIZIO CDN, decrypt it, valid=
ate the decrypted image and provide it to the TV OS for installation.</p></=
td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
